olive oil
3 garlic
20 g plant-based butter
1.25 cup water
1 packet jasmine rice
1 packet Smooth Dory Fillets
1 packet Asian Greens
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
drizzle sesame oil
1 packet Korean Stir-Fry Sauce
1 packet ginger paste
1 packet Plant-Based Mayo

• Finely chop garlic.
• In a medium saucepan, heat the plant-based butter with a dash of olive oil over medium heat. Cook 1/2 the garlic until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Add the water and a generous pinch of salt and bring to the boil. Add jasmine rice, stir, cover with a lid and reduce heat to low.
• Cook for 12 minutes, then remove from heat and keep covered until rice is tender and water is absorbed, 10-15 minutes.

TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam so don't peek!

• Meanwhile, discard any liquid from fish fillet packaging. Slice fish in half crossways to get 1 steak per person. Roughly chop Asian greens.

• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook shredded cabbage mix until tender, 4-5 minutes.
• Add the remaining garlic and Asian greens, and cook until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Add a drizzle of sesame oil and season. Transfer to a plate and cover to keep warm.

• Wipe out the frying pan, then return to medium-high heat with a generous drizzle of olive oil. When oil is hot, cook fish in batches until just cooked through, 5-6 minutes each side.

• Reduce heat to medium, then add Korean stir-fry sauce and ginger paste and cook, turning fish to coat, 1 minute.

• Divide garlic rice between bowls. Top with sesame veggies and Korean-style fish.
• Dollop over sriracha mayo to serve. Enjoy!